{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Instruments"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Class","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnfairLock"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"UnfairLock","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"class","title":"UnfairLock","externalID":"s:11Instruments10UnfairLockC"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Low-level lock that allows waiters to block efficiently on contention."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/instruments\/unfairlock"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments"]]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/init()"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/lock()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/try()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/unlock()","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/withLock(_:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods"},{"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/UnfairLock\/NSLocking-Implementations"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/objc(pl)NSLocking","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"UnfairLock"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"UnfairLock is an appropriate lock for cases where simple and lightweight mutual exclusion is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"needed. It can be intrusively stored inline in a data structure without needing a separate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allocation, reducing memory consumption and cost of indirection. For situations where something"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"more sophisticated like condition waits or FIFO ordering is needed, use appropriate higher level"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"APIs such as those from the pthread or dispatch subsystems."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The values stored in the lock should be considered opaque and implementation defined, they","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"contain thread ownership information that the system may use to attempt to resolve priority","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"inversions.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This lock must be unlocked from the same thread that locked it, attempts to unlock from a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"different thread will cause an assertion aborting the process.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This lock must not be accessed from multiple processes or threads via shared or multiply-mapped"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"memory, because the lock implementation relies on the address of the lock value and identity of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the owning process."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The name ‘unfair’ indicates that there is no attempt at enforcing acquisition fairness, e.g. an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unlocker can potentially immediately reacquire the lock before a woken up waiter gets an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"opportunity to attempt to acquire the lock. This is often advantageous for performance reasons,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"but also makes starvation of waiters a possibility."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This lock is suitable as a drop-in replacement for the deprecated OSSpinLock, providing much","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"better behavior under contention."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"List of Tools","identifiers":["doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/BytesConstructibleNumber","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/Endianness","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/DebounceFunction","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/DebounceFunctionConfiguration","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/HexStringDataDecoder","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/HexStringDataDecoderError","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/LLDB","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/WeakShared","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/Pointer","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/SecureRandom","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/SecureRandomError","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/Timer","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/LineByLineReader","doc:\/\/instruments.Instruments\/documentation\/Instruments\/LinewiseReader","doc:\/\/instru